  <title>CMake Macro Guards</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>CMake option</keyword>
    <keyword>compile guard</keyword>
    <keyword>diagnostic build</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_BOOTSTRAP_ITB_BYPASS</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_CHIPSET_DIAG</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_DEBUG_STEP</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_DIAGNOSTIC_LOGGING</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_FP_SOFTFLOAT</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_MEMDIAG</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_PA_DUMP</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_TRACE_HOOKS</keyword>
    <keyword>EMULATR_USE_OS_PAGES</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">CMake Macro Guards</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">A number of EmulatR behaviors are selected at build time through CMake options that define compile-guard macros, rather than at run time. This keeps diagnostic and debug scaffolding out of the shipping hot path: a guard that is off compiles to nothing. The options are set in the CMake configuration (for example through Qt Creator) and define the matching <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_*</text> macro for the build.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Build / behavior options</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="4" colcount="2" style="border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:solid; head-row-background-color:#00ffff; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <thead style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">Guard</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">Effect</text></para>
        </td>
      </thead>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_DEBUG_STEP</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Restores an -O0 build of the per-instruction pipeline step for single-step debugging. Off by default so the hot loop ships optimized.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_FP_SOFTFLOAT</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Selects the SoftFloat compute backend for floating point instead of the native host path, for bit-exact host-independent results.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_USE_OS_PAGES</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Selects the OS-page (VirtualAlloc / mmap) backing mode for guest memory.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Diagnostic / trace guards</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="8" colcount="2" style="border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:solid; head-row-background-color:#00ffff; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <thead style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">Guard</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="" style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">Effect</text></para>
        </td>
      </thead>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_TRACE_HOOKS</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Compiles in the per-step trace hooks used to capture an execution trace.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_MEMDIAG</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Compiles in the memory-diagnostic instrumentation (the cycle-windowed fetch / load / store dumps).</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_CHIPSET_DIAG</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Enables chipset-level diagnostic output.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_DIAGNOSTIC_LOGGING</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Enables the broader diagnostic logging path.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_PA_DUMP</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Compiles in physical-address dump instrumentation.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_BOOTSTRAP_ITB_BYPASS</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Debug only: bypasses the ITB for the known reset / PAL entry page during bring-up. Must be removed before relying on permission bits or ASN isolation.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_TRACE_CONSOLE / EMULATR_ISADIAG</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Console-trace and ISA-diagnostic channels.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The default build leaves the diagnostic guards off; they are turned on only when chasing a specific problem, because the instrumentation they add (especially the memory and trace hooks) is heavy enough to change runtime substantially. Runtime behavior that does not need a recompile is controlled instead by the <text styleclass="Code Example">EMULATR_*</text> environment variables.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
